Structure that connects multiple different (low and high) values across different graphs like spectrums
With a cross-graph connection like this, a query for a 'low relevance, low volatility, and/or high complexity' structure has a 'base solution' to try.
"Connections that haven't been applied yet" are similarly trivial to identify on this graph. When these graphs are arranged on a spectrum of similarity, 'maximally different or similar connections" are similarly trivial to identify.
